ain_2534068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 24, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yfn1665702970610.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yfn1665702970610.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yfn1665702970610.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yfn1665702970610\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Naming Rules for Sybase\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__section_v3x_b51_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d957634e54\">Table names</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__p_d60446e1_d60447e1_d60448e1\">Letters, numbers, dollar signs (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code>)\n            and underscores (_) are allowed. The first character must be a letter. Table names may\n            be between one and 30 characters long. Uniface only accepts uppercase names in the\n            application model definition but creates all lowercase names. Sybase, on the other hand,\n            allows a mixture; you can correctly reference mixed-case table names via assignment\n            tables.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__note_iqx_c51_kcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If an entity in the application model is called\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">TABLE1</code>, even if the assignment file refers to it in uppercase as\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">TABLE1</code>, the connector will create a table with the lowercase name\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">table1</code>. If the assignment file refers to this table with a name that\n            differs in any way from the model name, including the same name with a mixed case, for\n            example <code class=\"ph codeph\">Table1</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">TableOne</code>, the connector uses the\n            exact name of the assignment.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__p_d60449e1_d60450e1_d60451e1\">The names of Sybase stored procedures and triggers are\n            created using the table name as a base. If the table name is longer than 21 characters,\n            the trigger or procedure name is created using only the first 21 characters of the table\n            name. Therefore, table names must be unique in the first 21 characters for all\n            platforms.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__section_h5h_d51_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d957634e87\">Field names </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yfn1665702970610__p_d60455e1_d60456e1_d60457e1\">The same rules apply except that field names cannot be\n            renamed in the assignment file.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Naming Rules for Sybase Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 24, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Naming Rules for Sybase Table names Letters, numbers, dollar signs ( $ ) and underscores (_) are allowed. The first character must be a letter. Table names may be between one and 30 characters long. Uniface only accepts uppercase names in the application model definition but creates all lowercase names. Sybase, on the other hand, allows a mixture; you can correctly reference mixed-case table names via assignment tables. Note: If an entity in the application model is called TABLE1 , even if the assignment file refers to it in uppercase as TABLE1 , the connector will create a table with the lowercase name table1 . If the assignment file refers to this table with a name that differs in any way from the model name, including the same name with a mixed case, for example Table1 or TableOne , the connector uses the exact name of the assignment. The names of Sybase stored procedures and triggers are created using the table name as a base. If the table name is longer than 21 characters, the trigger or procedure name is created using only the first 21 characters of the table name. Therefore, table names must be unique in the first 21 characters for all platforms. Field names The same rules apply except that field names cannot be renamed in the assignment file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}